<br>
HF smiled at the two of them as he sat behind his desk and gazed at the screen long enough to determine that a document had just recently been encrypted.  HF entered the code and began to read.<br>
<br>
Cait had managed to get all the information he had asked for along with several parts essential for weapons repair and some less than edible rations.  Edible or not they would serve to keep some of the weaker ones from being denied food so that the rest could go on.  Many owed Caitriona their lives and they would never know it.<br>
<br>
Looking up he saw that Cait must have sent Declan back out again while he was absorbed in her report.  Usually focusing on anything to the exclusion of all others was a luxury a Nietzschean could ill afford, but HF knew he could trust Cait completely.  She was one of the very few in which he had absolute trust.<br>
<br>
He was about to comment on the report when the console in front of him began to flash.  A moment later his speculatative smile turned into a minor scowl.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
&quot;It seems that we have been invited to dinner on the Hetupratyaya...  Apparently her Captain wishes to shoot the breeze after as well.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>HF sighs as he shifts in his seat, suddenly tense</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
&quot;I hate this kind of crap...&quot;<br>
