<br>
&quot;Since you seem to have the dining arrangements under control,&quot; Sunyata told the Hetupratyaya, &quot;I'm headed to engineering lab one to test the cloaking boosters.  I don't want our gift to fail the Tyrants.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;My development and testing was as thorough as yours will be.  I didn't miss anything,&quot; the Hetu protested.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm not suggesting that you erred.  I just want to be tactually familiar with them for description and installation purposes.  Unless you were planning on installing them on the Sardaria and the Ferocitas Invictus yourself,&quot; Sunyata teased her ship.<br>
<br>
As she strode toward the engineering lab, Sunyata asked the Hetu about security arrangements for the dinner.  &quot;All labs, shops and bays will be locked and electronically barred for the duration of the Tyrant visit,&quot;  the Hetu replied.  &quot;The Tyrants can travel the ship freely with you or the XO.  They will not be permitted to enter essential areas unescorted until you grant them clearance.&quot;<br>
<br>
Once in the lab, Sunyata tested the cloaking boosters.  Made of strong, lightweight materials, the boosters looked like small metal spheres.  Once installed their unassuming appearance would make them difficult for any enemy to discover.  &quot;You do quality work, Hetu,&quot; Sunyata told her ship as she headed back to her quarters.  <br>
<br>
She changed into a pair of tight, but flexible, black pants and tucked the ends of a button-down, black silk shirt into the pant's waistband.  Then she sat, twirling the cloaking boosters in her fingers, and meditated briefly on the concept of quality while she awaited LT's notification that their guests had arrived.  Master Lao maintained that &quot;The quality of an abode is in its location, / The quality of the heart is in its depths, / The quality of giving lies in trust, / The quality of correct governance lies in orderly rule, / The quality of an enterprise depends on ability, / The quality of movement depends on timing.&quot;  The All willing, her timing was right and trusting the Tyrants enough to give them the cloaking boosters was the correct move.  <br>
<br>
Her Hetupratyaya was in pristine condition and twice the size of the Tyrant ships.  Even standard Wolverine battleships were widely known for their structural integrity, maneuverability, defenses and armaments; but the Hetupratyaya exceeded them.  The Hetu was a colony class battleship.  Sunyata's was only the thirteenth such ship ever christened on her homeworld.  This mission represented a vast expenditure of Wolverine resources.  At a time when no other pride offered support to the Tyrants, her help would likely be met with suspicion.  Nevertheless, help she would, presuming she could discover where she stood with the remnants of the pride.  Whether the Tyrants wanted her help made little difference.  As far as Wolverine pride was concerned, this little band of Nietzscheans was her albatross.  <br>
