</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Displaced ~ Tyrant RP (Rated R)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:gray;font-size:small;">LT informed Sunyata that the messages had been sent and she was waiting for replies. She then sat back and scanned the reports she had called for again. There was nothing new in any of them, no matter how much she wanted there to be.<br>
<br>
Where was XT? The longer it took to find him, the less likely it was they would find him alive, and she just didn't, couldn't accept that possibility. She knew Sca wouldn't either. Unless she saw his dead body, she would continue to look and hope to find her mate alive. XT was too good a survivor and had already survived situations that would have killed an ordinary Niet, and she just knew in her heart they would find him or he would find them. Failure was not an option in this instance.<br>
<br>
