<br>
Sunyata gave a little nod as she detached herself from the Hetupratyaya.  She retracted her boneblades and unrolled and re-buttoned the cuffs of her shirtsleeves.  Exiting the Captain's AI interface the same way she entered it, Sunyata then left her cabin and proceeded through the ship's corridors to Command.  <br>
<br>
Entering Command, Sunyata smiled at her XO.  Her own clothes were designed for functionality and comfort; but Sunyata was pleased to see her XO's choice of more festive attire.  The woman looked forward to seeing her family again and with good reason.  The All willing, she would find a way to gift her XO with more such interaction.  She hoped again that the other captains would bring their children with them.  Though she knew it would be difficult for them to trust her enough to risk it, Orion seemed terribly lonesome.  She might be wrong; but she didn't think he had seen any of his pridemates since LT and his separation from the rest of the family when matters came to a head on Idun.  <br>
<br>
&quot;You look great,&quot; Sunyata told her XO.  &quot;I bet you can hardly wait to see your family again.  Any response to our invitation yet?  Will our guests arrive soon?&quot; she queried.  <br>
