<br>
It was then that LM began to reflect on the events of the past year and on one event in particular.........</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>It was a dark room lit only by candles and filled with chanting <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Cuimhne cuimhne  Lassair ícaim cuimhne  Geal ícaim ícaim cuimhne.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Twelve priestesses, not Wayists, some other obscure sect stood around her anointing her with oils. The room had a heady, smoky air to it from burning herbs with a very unusual smell. <br>
<br>
A priestess passed her a cup and bade her drink. Curious as to it's contents she dubiously consumed the bitter tasting liquid but was relieved when all twelve priestesses did the same.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Cuimhne cuimhne  Lassair ícaim cuimhne  Geal ícaim ícaim cuimhne.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
The chanting got louder, faster. LM began to feel very light-headed and as though she were on fire. Then pictures of her homeworld, her mother, father and the other wives, her siblings, half siblings and cousins, her children, Caer, Morrigan, Cahan, and that little boy who was only a baby when she disappeared.......... <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&quot;Cuimhne cuimhne  Lassair ícaim cuimhne  Geal ícaim ícaim cuimhne.&quot;</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <br>
<br>
The chanting was reaching a crescendo now and she was beginning to feel connected, the strangest feeling that she could just reach out with her mind and touch anyone of those who mattered to her, call to them and they would hear her. And then the chanting stopped and finally it happened. She could picture another darkened room and a child being taken out of her. Suddenly she sprang up off the bench on which she'd been lying, scattering herbs and oils everywhere, stood up and proclaimed loudly:<br>
<br>
&quot;I am Geal Firinne, Tyrant Pride, out of Maeve by Cuchulain! I will have my vengeance!&quot;  </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#001B55><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bslipstreambbs12353.showUserPublicProfile?gid=loverofpurple>Lover of Purple</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table style='Filter: Shadow(Color=#9445dd, Direction=225)'><tr><td><span class='user title'>Triumvir</span></td></tr></table></span><br>  Posts: 152<br> <font color=#EFD68C>(2/27/03 11:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fslipstreambbs12353frm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13.topic&index=37>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Displaced ~ Tyrant RP (Rated R)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>LoP shuddered and found himself once again on the Purple Horizon. The chess set gone. Something powerfull had shot through the area and yanked him out of his study of timelines.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Athena, report!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Excuse me sir? Nothing has happened. Are you okay? </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The ships AI responded. <br>
<br>
LoP stood up and moved around the quiet bridge. The ship was designed for a crew of six, but it could be ran by LoP alone. He stopped and poured himself a cup of coffee, one of the few Earth delights he liked, and sat back down in the command chair.<br>
<br>
The black knight was the answer, but how to get him to make the right moves? That one was very untrusting but had great strength of character, something LoP repsected in him. <br>
<br>
It was time that LoP said hello to his Tyrant friends. And foes. </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Athena, power up and contact the Tyrant ships. Request permission to dock.<br>
<br>
